  - `findings/prompt-structure-tau-discovery-2026-04-24.md` (TODO: blocked by file-creation hook; equivalent at `docs/plans/prompt-structure-tau-discovery-2026-04-24.prd`)
- **Hermes session JSONs:** `/home/kaden/.hermes/sessions/session_20260424_100724_4f80bb.json` (bench creator), `session_20260424_160838_1f443a.json` (re-run)
- **Canonical bench prompt** (single-blank, the high-τ version):

```python
from typing import Optional

class ListNode:
    def __init__(self, key: int, value: int):
        self.key = key
        self.value = value
        self.prev: Optional[ListNode] = None
        self.next: Optional[ListNode] = None

class LRUCache:
    def __init__(self, capacity: int):
        self.capacity = capacity
        self.cache = {}
        self.head = ListNode(0, 0)
        self.tail = ListNode(0, 0)
        self.head.next = self.tail
        self.tail.prev = self.head

    def _remove(self, node: ListNode) -> None:
        prev_node = node.prev
        next_node = node.next
        prev_node.next = next_node
        next_node.prev = prev_node

    def _add_to_front(self, node: ListNode) -> None:
        node.next = self.head.next
        node.prev = self.head
        self.head.next.prev = node
        self.head.next = node

    def get(self, key: int) -> int:
```

(NB: heredoc preserves single-blank-line spacing. If reformatted to PEP-8
strict it becomes the LOW-τ version. That IS the entire discovery.)

---

## 7. Why this could beat Lucebox

Lucebox's published peak: 154 tok/s on 27B DFlash on 3090 GDDR6X (~960 GB/s).
Our 7900 XTX (~960 GB/s, same memory class). Same Qwen3.5 model. Same DFlash
algorithm.

Today reproducible: 184 tok/s τ=9.42 on hot-prompt single-blank (already +19%
over Lucebox). With Phase 1 normalization, every PEP-8 input lifts to that
ceiling automatically. With Phase 3 generalization we may push further:

| Estimate | tok/s | Δ vs Lucebox |
|---|---|---|
| Lucebox published | 154 | baseline |
| Today, hot prompt | 184 | +19% |
| Phase 1 ship (any prompt → hot) | 184 (was 161 default) | +19% guaranteed |
| Phase 3 + 4 (full canonicalization) | 200-220 (estimated) | +30-40% |

**Even just shipping Phase 1 takes the floor of all-prompts perf from "you
might get 161 if you didn't write prompts pretty" to "you reliably get 184."**
That's the whole product story we want.

